# Kiosk backend (Tailscale)

The visitor API runs on the Linux backend reached over **Tailscale**, not only localhost.

| Field | Value |
|-------|--------|
| Tailscale machine name | `sbikioskbackend` |
| OS hostname | `sbikioskbackend` |
| MagicDNS (preferred for URLs) | `sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net` |
| Tailscale IPv4 | `100.70.199.32` |
| OS | Ubuntu 26.04 LTS (`7.0.0-15-generic`) |

**Typical app URL** (default app port): `http://sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:8000` (or `http://100.70.199.32:8000`).

**TLS**: MagicDNS hostname may not have an HTTPS cert yet; use HTTP unless TLS is configured on the app.

**Secrets**: Never store Tailscale **node keys** or similar in this repo or in rules. If a node key was ever pasted into chat, rotate it in the Tailscale admin console if there is any exposure risk.

## Deploying code to the server (not your Windows laptop)

CUPS, Zebra scripts, `systemd`, and `/var/lib/visitor-kiosk` all run on **`sbikioskbackend`**, reached over **Tailscale SSH** (MagicDNS or `100.70.199.32`). After editing the repo on Windows, sync to `~/visitor-kiosk` on the server using one of:

- **Git** (if the repo has a remote): commit/push from Windows, then on the server `cd ~/visitor-kiosk && git pull`.
- **scp over Tailscale** from **PowerShell** (project root). User/host: `sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net`. If `scp` says permission denied on the server dirs, run once on the server: `chmod u+w ~/visitor-kiosk/app ~/visitor-kiosk/templates ~/visitor-kiosk/deploy`.

**Canonical sync commands** (copy as-is from `visitor-kiosk` root):

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\stewa\OneDrive\Desktop\Courser AI projects\visitor-kiosk"
```

**App Python (`app/`):**

```powershell
scp .\app\main.py .\app\schemas.py .\app\badge.py sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/app/
```

**Templates:**

```powershell
scp .\templates\index.html sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/templates/
```

**Deploy scripts / ZPL:**

```powershell
scp .\deploy\install-server.sh .\deploy\zebra-print-test.sh .\deploy\zebra-test.zpl sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/deploy/
```

**Requirements (when `requirements.txt` changed):**

```powershell
scp .\requirements.txt sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/
```

**Typical code + UI together (one line):**

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\stewa\OneDrive\Desktop\Courser AI projects\visitor-kiosk"; scp .\app\main.py .\app\schemas.py .\app\badge.py sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/app/; scp .\templates\index.html sbikioskbackend@sbikioskbackend.tail96d5df.ts.net:~/visitor-kiosk/templates/
```

**After sync on the server:** `sudo systemctl restart visitor-kiosk` (and `cd ~/visitor-kiosk && ./venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt` if dependencies changed).

Then run install/test commands **on the server SSH session**, not on localhost.

Badge printing uses CUPS on the server over **USB only** (not Ethernet): set **`ZEBRA_CUPS_QUEUE`** (same name as `lpstat -p`) on the `visitor-kiosk` systemd service. If unset, submissions still save; no print is attempted. Plug in the Zebra, add a raw/ZPL queue at `http://127.0.0.1:631/`, then set `ZEBRA_CUPS_QUEUE` to that queue name. Test: `bash deploy/zebra-print-test.sh YourQueueName`.
